Package: journalabbr
Type: Package
Title: Journal Abbreviations for BibTeX Documents
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("ShuCai Zou",email = "zscmoyujian@163.com",role =c("aut","cre")),
            person("Yu Chen", email = "chengyuxuezhe@163.com", role =c("aut")))
Description: Due to reference management software (e.g Zotero, Mendeley) export Bib file journal abbreviation is not detailed enough, and JabRef software provides a large number of journal abbreviation comparison table, but in JabRef management journal abbreviation, often due to memory error, resulting in software crash, so the journalabbr package only abbreviate the issue field of Bib file, and then output new Bib file for other software (for example Texstudio) to generate a reference format with journal abbreviations
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/zoushucai/journalabbr
BugReports: http://github.com/zoushucai/journalabbr/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: data.table, bib2df, stringr, dplyr, purrr, stringi, usethis, rlang, httr
Suggests: testthat, knitr, rmarkdown, ggplot2, tidyr
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Date: 2020-07-10
